    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `vim.diagnostic.Opts.VirtualLines.current_line` set to true, diagnostic display is changed from virt text to virt line for the current line.\nIt happens immediately as soon as the cursor is placed on the line (`CursorMoved` event) and that causes text to jump when scrolling or moving the cursor by holding down \"j\" or \"k\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt would be great to be able to debounce the swap of presentation so that diagnostics remain as virt text until the cursor has stopped on a line.\n\nI can work on this if it gets greenlit. ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "SGTM but would like to avoid yet another bespoke \"debounce\" implementation, so please consider reusing an existing one. Doesn't need to be a public interface like https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38999 , that is something we will work towards as we collect the common cases into one place.\n\nThe shared impl can live in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua` as a private `_debounce` function.",
